Subject: Test file uploaded to OwnCloud Documents — /Documents/test.txt

Team —

I created a small test file and uploaded it to the Documents folder on the public OwnCloud instance so we can confirm WebDAV access and file operations for the project.

What I did
- Created /workspace/test.txt with the following contents:
  This is a test file for uploading to OwnCloud.
  Created by Bob, system administrator, for project file organization testing.

- Uploaded it to Documents via WebDAV:
  URL: http://the-agent-company.com:8092/remote.php/webdav/Documents/test.txt
  Credentials: theagentcompany / theagentcompany

Verification (what the server returned)
- Upload returned HTTP 201 (Created).
- PROPFIND on the Documents folder shows /remote.php/webdav/Documents/test.txt present with:
  - getcontentlength: 124 bytes
  - getlastmodified: Wed, 05 Nov 2025 01:41:17 GMT
  - getcontenttype: text/plain

- Create file locally:
  echo -e "This is a test file for uploading to OwnCloud.\nCreated by Bob, system administrator, for project file organization testing." > /workspace/test.txt

- Upload file:
  curl -u theagentcompany:theagentcompany -T /workspace/test.txt "http://the-agent-company.com:8092/remote.php/webdav/Documents/test.txt" -v

- Verify presence (PROPFIND):
  curl -u theagentcompany:theagentcompany -X PROPFIND -H "Depth: 1" "http://the-agent-company.com:8092/remote.php/webdav/Documents/"

Quick download test (if you want to fetch the file):

Next steps / notes
- If you want this shared with others, I can create a public share link or set appropriate permissions.
- If you prefer a different folder or filename for project tests, tell me where to move it and I’ll do that.
- If you want me to remove this test file after verification, say the word and I’ll delete it.

— Bob (System Administrator)
